# Chief — environment variables.
# Copy to .env.local and fill in. NEVER commit real values; .env* is gitignored.

# --- Supabase (Phase 1) ---
# Project settings → API. The anon key is safe for the browser; RLS enforces access.
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project-ref.supabase.co
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-key
# Service-role key (Project settings → API → service_role). Used ONLY by the
# Proactive Chief webhook (/api/events/pipedream), which has no user session —
# it verifies the per-trigger token, then writes scoped to that user. Leave
# blank to keep proactive events off; every other path uses the anon key + RLS.
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=

# --- Anthropic (REQUIRED — Chief runs on it; also powers KB classify-on-save
#     and merge). Get a key at console.anthropic.com. ---
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=
# Optional override; defaults to the chief.model setting (claude-opus-4-8).
# ANTHROPIC_MODEL=claude-opus-4-8

# --- Voyage embeddings (optional — semantic KB search; without it the KB
#     degrades gracefully to full-text search) ---
# VOYAGE_API_KEY=

# --- Google / Gmail (Phase 4 — the inbox) ---
# Your OWN Google Cloud OAuth client (sovereign: your project, your consent
# screen, your tokens — stored only in your own database). Setup:
#   1. Create a Google Cloud project; enable the "Gmail API" and the
#      "Gmail MCP API" (gmailmcp.googleapis.com).
#   2. Google Auth Platform → configure the consent screen; under Data Access
#      add scopes: gmail.modify, gmail.compose, gmail.send.
#   3. Create an OAuth client (Web application) with redirect URI
#      https://YOUR-DOMAIN/api/google/callback (and http://localhost:3000/api/google/callback for dev).
#   4. Put the client ID/secret here, deploy, then tap Connect Gmail on the
#      Inbox screen.
# GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=
# GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=
